text: So, this is basically just another comedy with the same old formula of a wacky detective, but just with Sherlock Holmes sprinkled on top? How original. And why not add in Will Ferrell and John C. Reilly doing their same old comedy routine and rehashed jokes. I love comedies, but why do people waste their money seeing the same old formulas over and over again in theaters, especially when you can tell the studios are putting very little effort into making it anything but the same old thing, just with minor changes, all to make easy money? There is nothing really new with this, and if you want a wacky detective movie, go watch some of the original Pink Panther movies, and if you want a Will Ferrell and John C. Reilly comedy, just go watch any of the movies they have done together, because they do the same routine and jokes every single time.
